261014670.text: "We therefore examined the ability of WISP1 to modulate the phosphorylation of AMP activated protein kinase (AMPK), which can inhibit mTOR activity [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], tuberous sclerosis complex 2 (TSC2), that also blocks mTOR activity [XREF_BIBR], and Akt1 and p70S6K."
